    <h2>1. OnRecord Title — Best Overall</h2>
    <p>OnRecord Title was built by title industry veterans who got tired of watching national companies deliver mediocre service. Owner Keli Ivie brings 25+ years of experience, and the team collectively has 36+ years in title and escrow.</p>
    <p><strong>What sets them apart:</strong> 2-day title commitments when the industry average is 5-7. Mobile closings anywhere in Utah. When you call, you get Keli or Ciara — not a receptionist. Volume pricing for agents and loan officers who send consistent business. Licensed under Utah Insurance Dept. Agency License No. 976568.</p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Realtors, loan officers, and builders who need speed, reliability, and a title company that actually picks up the phone.</p>

    <h2>2. Cottonwood Title — Strong Local Alternative</h2>
    <p>Cottonwood Title is a well-established independent title company along the Wasatch Front. They offer solid service and have a good reputation among Utah real estate professionals. Turnaround times are competitive at 3-5 days, though they don't match OnRecord's 2-day standard. Mobile closings are available in some areas.</p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Agents looking for a reliable local alternative with an established track record.</p>

    <h2>3. Metro National Title — Good Regional Option</h2>
    <p>Metro National Title operates across Utah with multiple office locations. They offer competitive pricing and can handle volume, though individual service quality varies by location and assigned officer. Title commitment turnaround averages 3-5 days.</p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Professionals who need multi-location coverage and don't mind working with different officers.</p>

    <h2>4. First American Title — National Chain</h2>
    <p>First American is one of the largest title companies in the country. They have brand recognition and financial stability, but Utah-based agents frequently report slower turnarounds (5-7+ days), difficulty reaching their assigned officer, and a more impersonal experience. Calls typically route through a centralized system before reaching local staff.</p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Transactions requiring a nationally recognized underwriter or multi-state deals.</p>

